##26 days on air, I deleted my suicide note

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Zhao Siwei, an intern from Wuhan, is a reporter for the paper

Wu Kang, a 25-year-old recovering from new crown pneumonia, has posted more than 50 messages since his first appeal for help was posted at around 21:00 on January 23. His followers have risen from 1,000 to 1.79 million.

These micro-blogs recorded his helplessness from the onset of hospitalization, suffering from illness, the warmth of the company of relatives and friends, the dedication of medical care and patient diagnosis and treatment, the feeling of being encouraged by netizens and the joy of recovery and discharge from the hospital.

"Xiao Wu@bigwugod" the mood, the state of the body through the text "stab" through the screen to the fans who follow him every day, "how are you today? " "How's it going? " Waiting for "Xiao Wu@bigwugod" to update Weibo has become the expectation of many fans.

When helpless, bitter encounter love, family, friendship, a condensed 26 days to seek medical history can be "live" to all.

In an interview with thepaper.cn, Wu Hong listed several people to be grateful for, and he felt that this special new year 2020 would be enough to make him remember.

"This is my new life, " he said

Here is Wu Kang's dictation:

My name is Wu Kang (not my real name) , is a person who wrote a suicide note and deleted the new crown pneumonia patients, and now I recovered.

The first time I woke up from a deep sleep in the intensive care unit, I saw the injection of the nurse sister back to write "all good" two words, she joked with me, she is younger than me, I should not call her sister.

Before I left the hospital, I saw a sister nurse whose name was reversed to read "hope" and whose protective suit also said "hope" .

The persistence of their medical staff has given US patients hope.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A yellow wristband worn by Wu Kang during his hospital stay

Father Secretly in the hospital line, "drive" not to leave

One of the mysteries of life is its uncertainty, like when I got a new coronavirus.

On January 19, I had a quick meal at the Hankou Railway Station for an hour and a half. That afternoon, feel some physical discomfort, "no strength" , the night appeared diarrhea, high fever and other symptoms, fever to 39 degrees.

At that time, almost all of my friends and relatives, no one has the symptoms of new pneumonia, I thought I just eat bad belly, has been in accordance with the ordinary fever treatment. After eating the fever medicine and cold medicine that my girlfriend bought for me, my fever subsided but I had diarrhea crazily, which means I was "shitting water" .

On the 20th, when Academician Zhong Nanshan told the media that there were signs of human to human transmission of NCP, my girlfriend told me the news. I began to wonder if I had it, but none of my friends and colleagues got it, so I continued to take the medicine in bed. Fortunately, I didn't have a fever, but the diarrhea persisted.

On the 21st, the fever returned to me, at 38.8 degrees. My limbs ached, my cough grew worse, and I began to feel strange as I coughed bloody sputum in the shower. I quickly separated my girlfriend from me and told her not to come.

I immediately went to the armed police hospital, Hubei Provincial Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine inspection. After the doctor of Traditional Chinese Medicine Hospital checks, tell me double lung infection, basically can confirm is new coronary pneumonia. The bad news was that I couldn't be admitted to the hospital, so I had to go directly to another hospital for medication and injections.

Inquiry found that the seventh hospital in Wuhan can be hospitalized, but rushed to the hospital is being renovated, the next day to enter, and I rushed to Wuchang Hospital.

The doctors at Wuchang also looked at me and saw that my symptoms were similar to those of new coronary pneumonia. They gave me antiviral drugs and a hospital admission certificate. Told me I wouldn't have a bed until 6:00 the next day.

Shortly after 11:00 that night, when my parents heard that the No. 7 Hospital in Wuhan was open to patients like me, my father secretly helped me to get in line. He waited for a long time just to let me sleep a little longer. Then he called me up and told me to go to the doctor.

I was upset. I told him to go. He wouldn't listen. When I got there, I "chased" him away. He hid outside in the glass window and peeped at me. I couldn't "chase" him.

In the Seventh Hospital in Wuhan, doctors said after examination that my symptoms are basically new coronary pneumonia, but test paper ran out, I can not provide a diagnosis and hospitalization, let home isolation.

I asked him, "am I just going to go back? " Remember the young doctor looking at me calmly and apologetically and saying, "I feel worse than you, because I've seen a lot, but I can't help it. "

After I talked my dad out of it, I went back to my place and started isolating myself. I called my friends as a farewell, said what I do not remember, the most memorable sentence is "may not have me after this person. "

At 4 pm on the 22nd, I went to Wuchang Hospital with my hospital card. I waited until 6 pm and was told the bed was full and could not be admitted. On-site waiting for the signature of the patients were persuaded to return, the nurse said the only director can sign to save the patient, no director signed the hospital bill void.

At this time I was breathing very fast, back lung location has a clear sense of weight-bearing, cough cough cough blood aggravation, limb weakness. Talking to my patients, and they told me that my rate of symptoms was very high.

I had no choice but to go back home again, isolated, parents and girlfriends refused to come over to take care of.

At that time can check the designated hospital, only accept critically ill patients, know a few patients are still in vain. I really do not know my situation, when will suddenly critically ill, when can be hospitalized, can only rely on friends, family, girlfriend's encouragement to resist.

On the other hand, I am also very worried about my contact with relatives and friends infected, the phone learned that my mother has mild symptoms, especially scared, I do not want them to taste my plight.

The next day, Wuhan "closed the city. ".

At 21:48 on the night of the "closing of the city" , I posted my first post related to the new crown pneumonia, describing what happened to me the other day and what happened that day, at the BOTTOM@ARE "Wuhan Publication" , "Wuhan Mayor Line" , "Wuhan Municipal Commission of Health" and various media.

I can't think of anything I can do to help myself.

Tens of thousands of people commented, liked, and retweeted the post, both encouraging me in the comments area and sending me private messages, while also retweeting their calls for help. I've never met you before, and I'm touched.

On the 24th, a new symptom appeared in my body. Every few minutes, when I was about to fall asleep, there was a sound in my chest that woke me up. It's still a cough, aching limbs, crazy diarrhea. Mom and dad made a dozen dishes sent to the door, but I put them into the refrigerator, really can not eat. I wish I wasn't in the hospital. I just need a shot.

On the 25th, things took a turn. My community registered my information, and helped me to make an appointment for a doctor, let me wait for news. My company also know about my situation, colleagues are very concerned about me, actively contact the greetings and bought for me a oximeter, said that is the follow-up drugs will also help me buy.

On the 26th, my fever persisted and my condition became very bad. The community arranged a battery car to take me and another patient to Wuchang Hospital for treatment. I finally got my injection. Doctors and nurses are very good, very careful to tell me how to walk, how to line up.

That day, I got a message from a young sick couple I had met at a Wuchang Hospital. I was happy to hear that they were getting better. I remember the day we met, I was also inspired, told them, "if God can let us through this difficult time, must love life, thanksgiving life. " Did not think that the brother can always remember.

In fact, I have always thought that if I "carry" through, I will be grateful for the life of the Every Little Thing, and no longer quarrel with their families and girlfriends, more and friends get together. I also want to go to the scene to see Ti China Judun (Ti is the DOTA 2 annual World Cup) , to see the Lpl three-time champion, to see Wei Shen 17 champion, to see China to come out of several NBA players, to see the National Football World Cup...

You write a suicide note and then you delete it

Since January 19 symptoms, toss about for several days, 26, I finally admitted to the Wuchang Hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
During Wu Kang's hospital stay

When I moved in, I didn't know what was happening to me. I didn't know until I got out of the hospital. My girlfriend asked a lot of friends to find out that I was in the ICU. But the whole time, the paramedics and my friends, they never told me. My friends would send me funny videos every day, and the medical staff would talk to me every day without mentioning the words "critical" or "critical" .

But I can feel it in my bones. I'm not in a good place.

The night I checked in, two doctors gave me a CT, when a doctor after seeing the CT said, "how only three days (doctors from the 23rd) so? " I listen to the heart of a chill. The chief doctor pulled the doctor away and told me, "don't worry, it's not serious, you're young and you can be cured. " I cried. I knew it was probably a white lie, but I was really grateful to him, i really appreciate it.

During the whole period of hospitalization, a lot of medicine and injections should be taken every day. At that time, I had secretly written a suicide note, but soon deleted.

The biggest challenge every day is oneself prop up to pull out oxygen tube to take medicine, medicine really too much. Early in the morning, before I get my shot, my dad would drop off the Ivig, and he'd leave it at the door, and then he'd turn around three times a day, and I wouldn't pick it up until he was long gone. I don't know how much longer I'm GonNa be playing with this Ivig, four or five a day. It's too expensive.

My parents and I only said the illness, but as for how bad the body, I dare to tell only friends.

I continued to post my daily status and treatment on Weibo, first as a cry for help, then as a way to share my symptoms in the hope of helping others. There are a lot of enthusiastic netizens will be tired of private messages to comfort me, encourage me, I can not reply one by one, every time to write a long article is on and off for a long time, the body is still very weak.

When we were in the hospital, the nurses would come every day at 7:00 to take our temperature, and anything above 37.2 was considered a fever, and anything above 95 was considered normal. If you need to draw blood for a routine blood test, start at 5:00 a.m.

February 3 that day, I sleep until 8:00, is that time to sleep "the deepest" a sleep, breakfast bean paste bag I love to eat, eat up. After getting up, to see the injection of the nurse sister back to write "all good" two words, she and I joke that she is younger than me, I should not call her sister.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
During Wu Kang's hospital stay, a nurse wrote "All right" on her back, implying that everything was going well

The average nurse is in their early 20s, and they're all young, some younger than me. They shuttled back and forth from room to room every day, pumping fluids, changing bottles, and anything else would ring the Bell, and the center of the nurses'station would ring, one after the other, rarely stopping. I'd breathe through my breath, and my goggles would be so steamy that my eyes would water involuntarily.

One time, the sister of a nurse who gave me the shot wrote "Sunny" on the back of her protective suit. She explained that she thought it was time to start clearing up after the epidemic had lasted so long? When the patients saw it, they joked, "no, it should say 'sunny to cloudy, ' Ha-ha. " The nucleic acid test was negative and everyone was looking forward to it.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There is an 80-year-old grandmother in our ward. She is very lovely. At the beginning of the meal are volunteers to send, grandma every day before eating as in prayer, "thank these volunteers, good people to send food. ".

On the 4th, I didn't have a fever for a few days, and on the 3rd night, the frequency of my chest cavity, which was hard to carry down, decreased a lot, only appeared about four or five times. But the cough was still there, and it was always going to be for the better, I told myself. This Day, when I hit the right hand can not get into the change to hit the left hand, no injection indwelling needle, both hands forearm and wrist are very painful, the doctor and I said the injection is a bit painful.

On the 5th, the sister of the nurse who shared the breakfast finally came again and told us how much breakfast we had? Another uncle in the same room asked for a bag of yogurt and said, "don't waste it. " We were all laughing, the mood was good all morning, and everyone was very optimistic. With the ward that "talk the most" aunt also discharged from the hospital, once in a while think she is a bit noisy, but the ward without her, suddenly become very quiet, I still a little not used to. But I'm sure she and her family will be thrilled.

On the 6th, no nurse sister came to give me an injection, because the head nurse informed me that I could pack up and go to the Shelter Hospital for quarantine. I was a little worried at first, because some comments on the Internet made me worry about the treatment conditions in the shelter. But I didn't make it because I had to continue the infusion. As it turned out, everyone was fine in the shelter, so there was no need to worry.

On the 8th, it's the Lantern Festival. I went for a CT scan, which was better than the day I was admitted (January 26) , but the cough was worse. In the evening, the hospital brought Tangyuan to the patient, and I was so excited that I thought there would be no food this year.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Feb. 8, the day of the Lantern Festival, hospitals prepare dumplings for such patients as Wu Kang

On the 9th, a sister of a nurse's protective clothing said "I am here! Thor! " I heard that Thor Mountain is also ready to start treating patients, the number of people receiving treatment will be more and more, the situation will be better and better, I hope the turning point will come soon.

On the 10th, the NUCLEIC ACID test turned negative for me and my grateful grandmother in the same room before every meal, and I almost burst into tears. This period of time, how many times in the death of wandering, the most difficult time to write a suicide note, crying good-bye and good friends, also do not dare to say to parents, now finally turn negative. The doctor gave me some medicine because my cough was beginning to bleed again.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On This Day, I saw a nurse sister protective clothing behind the word is "cloud energy, infinite. ". Combined with my own experience, I understand that the Internet users for our patients each care, for our patients are infinite.

I remember the day I came to the hospital, my fever did not subside, I was cold, I was unconscious, the nurse gave me a yellow bracelet, the doctor asked me to sign all kinds of notices, I was scared to death, i thought that is in case I "stand" not used to identify the identity, did not expect the yellow bracelet with me for so long, I also survived the most difficult period of time.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I want to give the nurse some milk tea

February 13, finally, two negative nucleic acid, I can go home from the hospital, but need to go home isolation for 14 days, wait a month to review.

Before leaving the hospital, I saw the name of a sister nurse, which in turn read "Hope" and was also written on her protective suit. The persistence of their medical staff gives hope to those of us who are sick.

The community sent a car to pick me up. The road was very windy. I asked the driver if I could slow down. He said yes. When I got home, I bowed to the driver and turned back to the house.

For sequelae, my discharge summary said that part of the location of the "fiber stove, " a little nervous. The doctor explained to me that in every serious case, there are basically fibrous foci or pulmonary fibers, which are like when you get hurt, and when you get better, you have scar tissue. "If the scar is big, it will have an effect; if the scar is small, it will have no effect. " So I also want to tell other patients not to worry too much, it is not as serious as blind guess.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
When we get back to the neighborhood, I need a seal on my front door, and I understand that during special times. The property's sister and I chat, brought me a lot of disinfectant and alcohol, as well as vegetables and medicine, so that the next community shopping. She put things in the door, a large bag, there are drugs have vegetables have dumplings, really very moved.

After coming home, I disinfected the house and the outside, and took a bath that had not been washed for twenty days. I felt very comfortable. Community property will regularly bring me food and daily necessities, physical condition needs to report three times a day to the community wechat. I think a little more strict community management, is a big step forward, because not all observers will be the same as me to stay at home.

During my stay at home, I calculated that I spent 25,180 yuan on pre-registration, drug purchase, and IMMUNOGLOBULIN transfusion at my own expense, and 11,000 yuan on post-diagnosis treatment. The expense of this part of the diagnosis can definitely be reimbursed.

From the onset of an infection, to self-medication, to a confirmed hospitalization, to recovery and discharge from the hospital, I would like to thank a lot of people, this difficult medical history is really unforgettable.

When I was still recovering, I said, "If I get better, I think I'm going to be the anti-body everyone says I'm going to be, " and I thought, I'm going to join them when I'm out of the observation period.

I contacted the Wuhan Blood Center, and so after the end of the observation period, the test is no problem, the first time to donate plasma. See The news of the introduction, said the recovery of the patient's body has antibodies, will be transfusion of plasma to critically ill patients, for them is "specific medicine. ".

I would also like to thank the hospital doctors and nurses, I have been to a period of time before all the hospitals, the order is basically stable, the patients are in line in good order.

The young doctor I met in the Seventh Hospital in Wuhan worked for four or five hours straight just while waiting in line. After I left at dawn, he was still waiting for patients in the consultation room. I don't know if his physical load was over the limit, but he didn't complain, just sat there, patient after patient, as if there was no end.

During my stay in the hospital, my sister, a nurse who took care of me, posted on my micro blog and often encouraged me. She said she loved drinking milk tea, but now she can't even drink it. I want to wait until the epidemic stabilizes, to the health care workers send Jinqi, but also must send a lot of milk tea.

Besides, I'd like to thank the community driver who brought me to the hospital, wearing protective clothing, for all the phone calls his family made while he was waiting for other patients. Weren't they scared? I'm sure they are, but they're still at their posts.

I remember once reading a private message on Weibo while lying in a hospital bed. One Netizen said that her wish for her 18th birthday on this day was to wish me safe and healthy. For such a valuable gift, I could only reply with "thank you" . Another netizen shared with me the heavy snow in their home. The snow was very heavy, and a thick layer was spread over the field. He told me to get well quickly and see many beautiful scenery.

In short, too much encouragement and touched, drive away my negative energy, let me actively cooperate with the treatment, overcome the disease.

Sincerely to say: Thank you!
